LAGOS – Qatar Airways Group celebrates its milestone 25th anniversary year of operation with its strongest financial performance reflected in its published annual report for 2021/22. The airline’s $1.54 billion financial year 2021-2022, represented 200 per cent above its highest annual historical profit. A statement by the media consultant to the airline in Nigeria stated that in the most difficult period ever in the global airline industry, the carrier credits its positive results to its agility and successful strategy, which continued to focus on customer needs and evolving market opportunities, as well as efficiency and the commitment of its worldwide employees. The statement hinted that the profit is not only a record for Qatar Airways Group, but also a record among all other airlines that have published financial results for this financial year worldwide. The airline’s overall revenue increased to $ 14.4 billion, up 78 per cent, compared to last year and a remarkable two per cent higher than the full financial year pre-COVID (2019/20). Passenger revenue increased by 210 per cent over the last year, due to the growth of the Qatar Airways network, increase in market share and higher unit revenue, for the second financial year in a row. Qatar Airways carried 18.5 million passengers, an increase of 218 per cent, compared to the same period last year. Qatar Airways Cargo remained the leading player in the world as its revenue experienced an impressive growth of 25 per cent over last year with the growth in cargo capacity (Available Tonne Kilometers) of 25 per cent annually. The group generated a strong EBITDA Margin of 34 per cent at QAR 17.7 billion (US$ 4.9 billion). EBITDA was higher than the previous year by QAR 11.8 billion (US$ 3.2 billion) due to streamlined, agile and fit-for-purpose operations across all business areas.